  "text": "Regarding methodological issues, selection bias needs consideration, since controls were recruited from non-cancer hospital outpatients. However, the distribution of diseases among randomly selected non-cancer controls of Aichi Cancer Center Hospital did not demonstrate any obvious feature in common, with reference to precancerous lesions or tobacco-related conditions [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, to access the quality and validity of our questionnaire, we compared non-cancer ACCH outpatients with subjects randomly selected from the electoral roll [CITATION_2] . We found that, with due consideration of age, sex, and season in the analysis, it is feasible to use non-cancer outpatients as controls.",
